---
import "../styles/global.css";
import Section from "../components/Section.astro";
import Pyramid from "../components/Pyramid.astro";
import Project from "../components/Project.astro";

const title = "equanimi.tech";
const description =
  "An independent research lab on the design of technology that cultivates equanimity.";
---
<!doctype html>
<html lang="en">
  <head>
    <meta charset="utf-8" />
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1" />
    <title>{title}</title>
    <meta name="description" content={description} />
    <meta name="color-scheme" content="light" />
    <meta name="robots" content="index,follow" />
    <meta property="og:title" content={title} />
    <meta property="og:description" content={description} />
    <meta property="og:type" content="website" />
    <meta property="og:url" content="https://equanimi.tech/" />
    <link rel="canonical" href="https://equanimi.tech/" />
    <link
      rel="preload"
      href="/fonts/Inter-Variable.woff2"
      as="font"
      type="font/woff2"
      crossorigin
    />
  </head>
  <body>
    <header class="masthead">
      <p class="wordmark">equanimi<span class="dot">.</span>tech</p>
      <p class="tagline">An independent research lab on the design of technology that cultivates equanimity.</p>
    </header>

    <main>
      {/* §1 OPENING */}
      <Section id="opening" className="opening">
        <p class="opening__text">Attention is all they need.<br/>Equanimity is what we deserve.</p>
      </Section>

      {/* §2 Reversal */}
      <Section id="reversal" eyebrow="The reversal">
        <div class="prose">
          <p>
            Engagement was a measurement choice. Click, dwell, share, convert:
            easy to count, easy to optimize, easy to sell. Over a decade, the
            metric became the product, and the product became the air we breathe.
          </p>
          <p>
            Calm Technology mapped the periphery. Humane Tech defended attention.
            Convivial Tech asked who serves whom. Each opened ground we still
            stand on. Equanimitech picks up where their questions end: what
            happens when AI fills the periphery, smooths the hijacking, and
            hides the seams.
          </p>
          <p>
            We are the research lab for that question. Not mindfulness apps. Not
            screen-time dashboards. Technology in which equanimity can survive
            contact with the digital world.
          </p>
        </div>
      </Section>

      {/* §3 Thesis */}
      <Section id="thesis" eyebrow="The thesis">
        <blockquote class="thesis">
          Engagement couples wanting to what feels good. Equanimity decouples
          them. Wanting driven by values. The gap between sensation and reaction
          is where choice lives. Most technology closes it. Equanimitech is the
          research lab widening it.
        </blockquote>
      </Section>

      {/* §4 Framework */}
      <Section id="framework" eyebrow="The framework">
        <p class="prose"><span>Three layers, each depending on the one below. Nine principles. Each with a design test.</span></p>

        <Pyramid />

        <div class="principle-tests" aria-label="Example principles">
          <div class="principle-test">
            <p class="principle-test__name">
              Local-First Ownership <span class="layer-tag">(Sovereignty)</span>
            </p>
            <p class="principle-test__q">
              Does this work offline? If our servers shut down tomorrow, does the
              tool keep working?
            </p>
          </div>
          <div class="principle-test">
            <p class="principle-test__name">
              Bounded Experiences <span class="layer-tag">(Awareness)</span>
            </p>
            <p class="principle-test__q">
              Does this interaction have a natural end? If the user stops, is that
              a feature?
            </p>
          </div>
          <div class="principle-test">
            <p class="principle-test__name">
              Fade-by-Design <span class="layer-tag">(Equanimity)</span>
            </p>
            <p class="principle-test__q">
              Success means the user needs the tool less over time, through
              internalization. If a user stopped using this after six months, would
              we celebrate or panic?
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>

        {/* pending-URL: link to full primer */}
        <p><a href="#">Read the primer →</a></p>
      </Section>

      {/* §5 Deeper question */}
      <Section id="deeper" eyebrow="The deeper question">
        <div class="deeper prose">
          <p>
            Engagement is what's easy to measure. Click, dwell, share, convert.
            But the metric doesn't just describe the thing; it shapes it. A
            platform optimized for engagement, sustained over years, makes humans
            more reactive. A platform optimized for something else would make
            humans something else. The honest question isn't whether AI will
            outpace human intellect. It already has, in narrow ways, and the
            trend continues. The honest question is whether the technology we
            build alongside it leaves room for what intellect alone has never
            reached.
          </p>
        </div>
      </Section>

      {/* §6 Research (was §7 Work) */}
      <Section id="work" eyebrow="Research">
        <p class="prose">Two research projects from the lab. Different scales. Same principles.</p>

        <div class="projects" style="margin-top: calc(var(--spacing) * 10);">
          <Project
            category="Sovereignty"
            name="Secretariat"
            tagline="Ambient context for AI, stamped by humans."
            body="The substrate for autonomous work where agents draft at volume, humans vouch for what matters, and no vendor sits in the middle. Local-first. Filesystem-authoritative. Built in the open."
            links={[
              { label: "Docs", href: "#" },
              { label: "GitHub", href: "#" },
            ]}
          />
          {/* pending-URL: Secretariat docs + GitHub */}

          <Project
            category="Awareness"
            name="Zenborg"
            tagline="The whiteboard, made software."
            body="Plan your day in three-word moments. Three at a time, three times a day, three days ahead. No streaks, no scores, no notifications. The constraints are the point."
            links={[
              { label: "Try it", href: "#" },
              { label: "Download", href: "#" },
            ]}
          />
          {/* pending-URL: Zenborg web + download */}
        </div>
      </Section>

      {/* §7 Writing (was Reading) */}
      <Section id="reading" eyebrow="Writing">
        <p class="prose">The lab's writing carries as much of the discipline as the projects.</p>

        <ul class="reading-list" style="margin-top: calc(var(--spacing) * 8);">
          <li>
            {/* pending-URL: Three Poisons of Engagement */}
            <a href="#"><span class="title">Three Poisons of Engagement</span></a>
            <span class="meta">The diagnosis, in three parts.</span>
          </li>
          <li>
            {/* pending-URL: Primer v0.2 */}
            <a href="#"><span class="title">Equanimitech Primer v0.2</span></a>
            <span class="meta">The full framework. Nine principles. The measurement gap.</span>
          </li>
          <li>
            {/* pending-URL: Mindful Cyborg */}
            <a href="#"><span class="title">Mindful Cyborg</span></a>
            <span class="meta">Ongoing essays.</span>
          </li>
        </ul>
      </Section>

      {/* §8 Door */}
      <Section id="door" eyebrow="The door">
        <div class="prose">
          <p>
            If you're building something in this direction, or thinking about it,
            write to the lab.
          </p>
          <a class="door__email" href="mailto:rafaba@hey.com">rafaba@hey.com</a>
        </div>
      </Section>
    </main>

    {/* §9 Footer */}
    <footer id="footer" class="footer">
      <div class="footer__inner">
        <div class="footer__cols">
          <div class="footer__col">
            <p class="footer__head">Research</p>
            {/* pending-URL: Secretariat */}
            <p><a href="#">Secretariat</a></p>
            {/* pending-URL: Zenborg */}
            <p><a href="#">Zenborg</a></p>
          </div>
          <div class="footer__col">
            <p class="footer__head">Writing</p>
            {/* pending-URL: Three Poisons */}
            <p><a href="#">Three Poisons of Engagement</a></p>
            {/* pending-URL: Primer v0.2 */}
            <p><a href="#">Equanimitech Primer v0.2</a></p>
            {/* pending-URL: Mindful Cyborg / Substack */}
            <p><a href="#">Mindful Cyborg</a></p>
          </div>
          <div class="footer__col">
            <p class="footer__head">Contact</p>
            <p><a href="mailto:rafaba@hey.com">rafaba@hey.com</a></p>
            {/* pending-URL: GitHub org */}
            <p><a href="#">GitHub</a></p>
          </div>
        </div>
        <p class="footer__base">
          Equanimitech, an independent research lab. 2026. Page source on
          {" "}<a href="#">GitHub</a>.
        </p>
      </div>
    </footer>
  </body>
</html>
